\pard\f0\fs28  Plants slightly hairy or almost glabrous at the base of the stem are known from two localities in Portugal and have been described as{\b  M. lusitanica} Schuster, {\i Feddes Repert.}{\b  74}: 85 (1967). They also resemble{\b  34}, and further investigation is needed.
