\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 32. M. stolonifera} (DC.) Gay ex Leresche & Levier,{\i  Deux Excurs. Bot.} 83 (1880). Like {\b 30} but smaller; hairs at base of stem appressed; stolons numerous in lower part of plant, often much-branched; leaves up to 2 × 1 cm; calyx up to 3 mm in fruit; limb of corolla 4-5 mm in diameter; nutlets 1·2 × 0·7 mm, ovoid, the rim only weakly developed. 2n = 24.{\i  Wet places; in mountains in the southern part of its range. W. Europe.} Br Hs Lu.
\par

